Sales By Day Sheet 17


1. Right on Sales by Size worksheet and select Duplicate. Rename the new sheet as Sales By Day.


2. Remove Pizza Size from Columns shelf. Drag and drop Order Date to Columns shelf, right click on it and select Weekday from the drop down options.

3. Right click on Y axis and select Edit axis. Under Range, select Fixed.

 Fixed Start = 0, Fixed End = 182, 877

Under Axis Titles, leave the title blank.

4. Right click on X axis label and select Edit axis. Under Range, select Fixed.

 Fixed Start = -0.447, Fixed End = 1.291

Under Axis Titles, leave the title blank.

5. Drag and drop Date Filter to Filters shelf and select only True option.

6. Click on Tooltip under marks and enter the following:

Weekday: <WEEKDAY(Order Date)>

 Total Sales:<SUM(Total Price)>

 Sales MoM:<AGG(Sales MoM %)>

 Avg Orders:<AGG(Avg Orders By Day)>

 Orders MoM:<AGG(Orders MoM %)>

 Avg Price:<AGG(Avg Order Price)>

 Avg Price MoM:<AGG(Avg Price MoM %)>

 Measure Names: <Measure Names>

Font = Tableau Book, Size = 8, Bold, Alignment = Left

7. Right click on Title, select Edit Title, add the title Sales by Day.
